WHEREAS, Mr. Hie's extensive experience in business will be valuable to the
Tennessee public utility commission; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 65-1-101, provides that each
appointment to the Tennessee public utility commission shall be confirmed by joint resolution
adopted by each house of the general assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby confirm the appointment of John Hie of Nashville to serve a six-
year term as a commissioner of the Tennessee public utility commission, such term to expire on
June 30, 2030.
